{"votes": {"funny": 0, "useful": 1, "cool": 1}, "user_id": "8KWAoyumKQJ0sSyN-TqK9g", "review_id": "vp-NKqs_AgKrS1_YIp2_DA", "text": "my family and i have enjoyed coming here on many occasions. my father and his side of the family are yucatecan and love the authenticity of it. chichen itza is located in a huge warehouse type building and while the restaurant itself might appear a bit dinky, let me assure you, the food served here is top notch. i usually order the cochinita pibil which is just slow roasted pork marinated in achiote sauce (among other things) and tastes sublime. i've also ordered the sopa de lima (brothy turkey soup with lime), brazo de reina (tamales filled with hard boiled eggs), and papadzules (tacos with hard boiled eggs). there's also a plate, \"el trio\", which isn't listed on the menu, but has now become my go-to dish and comes with a cochinita pibil taco, a panucho (fried corn tortilla stuffed with black beans and topped with shredded turkey, lettuce, avocado, and red onions), and a salbute (soft, fluffy corn tortilla topped with shredded turkey, lettuce, avocado and red onions). my grandparents (both vendors at olvera street) know the owner of this place and so he'll sometimes come over to our table to chat it up. overall this place is one of my favorites to go to, even if it's a long drive from where i live, to me it's well worth it.", "business_id": "vC_6J_nGyf4J8xt-Vu6Shw", "stars": 5, "date": "2011-07-13", "type": "review"}